This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with explaining the behavior of deep neural networks. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as deep neural networks are a popular tool in AI research. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel algorithm for approximating Shapley values, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, since the paper deals with deep neural networks, which are often used in computer vision tasks, it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
